'''Ardon "Vapor" Crell''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Moisture farmer/Legends|moisture farmer]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] who had joined the [[local 253]] sector of the [[Moisture Farmers of Tatooine]] organization by [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]]. A liaison between local 253 and the [[Crime lord/Legends|crime lord]] [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba the Hutt]], Crell was responsible for collecting the [[Water/Legends|moisture]] [[Farm/Legends|farmers]]' money and delivering it to the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] for protection against [[Tusken Raider/Legends|Tusken Raiders]]. In 4 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|ABY]], Crell was present in [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's Palace]] when [[Heroes of Yavin/Legends|several allies]] of Jabba's [[Prisoner/Legends|prisoner]] [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] [[Siege of Jabba's Palace|arrived]] in an attempt to rescue their companion. Those events led to Jabba sentencing Solo and companions [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] and [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] to [[Death/Legends|death]] at the [[Great Pit of Carkoon/Legends|Great Pit of Carkoon]]. Crell and other members of [[Jabba's criminal empire/Legends|Jabba's court]] accompanied the crime [[Lord/Legends|lord]] on the [[Luxury-class sail barge|luxury sail barge]] [[Khetanna/Legends|''Khetanna'']] in order to witness the executions. The captives [[Battle of the Great Pit of Carkoon|fought back]], however, and the ''Khetanna'' was ultimately destroyed.

==Biography==
[[File:Ardon1.png|thumb|left|154px|Ardon Crell (far left) during Leia Organa's capture by Jabba the Hutt]]
The [[Human/Legends|Human]] Ardon Crell lived during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], a conflict between the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]].<ref name="RotJ" /> By [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]],<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' establishes that the events of [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']] take place in [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]].</ref> he had become a [[Moisture farmer/Legends|moisture farmer]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]]<ref name="BtM" /> and joined [[local 253]], a sector of the [[Moisture Farmers of Tatooine]] organization. He had by then also acquired the nickname "Vapor."<ref name="CCG" /> Crell was chosen by his peers to serve as a liaison between local 253 and the [[Crime lord/Legends|crime lord]] [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba the Hutt]]. The [[Water/Legends|moisture]] [[Farm/Legends|farmers]] agreed to pay Jabba in exchange for protection from [[Tusken Raider/Legends|Tusken Raiders]], and Crell was responsible for both collecting and delivering the protection money.<ref name="BtM" />

In 4 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|ABY]],<ref name="NEC" /> Crell was present in the audience chamber of [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's Palace]] on Tatooine when Alliance leader [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]], disguised as the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Boushh/Legends|Boushh]], [[Siege of Jabba's Palace|arrived]] with the intention of rescuing her ally [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], who was [[Carbon-freezing/Legends|frozen]] in [[Carbonite/Legends|carbonite]] and hanging on the wall of the palace's courtroom. Organa arrived with the [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]], ostensibly her captive, and threatened to destroy the palace with a [[Class-A thermal detonator/Legends|thermal detonator]]. Like others in the Hutt's courtroom, Crell panicked at Organa's threat. Organa won the Hutt's favor but that [[Standard day/Legends|night]] [[Rescue of Han Solo/Legends|rescued]] Solo and attempted to escape the palace with him. Crell and others in the Hutt's palace accompanied the crime [[Lord/Legends|lord]] as he caught Organa and Solo, who were subsequently [[Prison/Legends|imprisoned]]. Their mutual ally [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] then arrived at the palace to demand the release of all three prisoners, but the Hutt dropped Skywalker into the pit of his pet [[Jabba's rancor/Legends|rancor]]. However, Skywalker [[Death/Legends|killed]] the [[Rancor/Legends|rancor]], prompting the Hutt to sentence Skywalker, Solo, and Chewbacca to death at the [[Great Pit of Carkoon/Legends|Great Pit of Carkoon]].<ref name="RotJ" />

Crell and other members of [[Jabba's criminal empire/Legends|Jabba's court]] accompanied the Hutt on the [[Luxury-class sail barge|luxury sail barge]] [[Khetanna/Legends|''Khetanna'']] in order to witness the execution of the captives. However, the captives [[Battle of the Great Pit of Carkoon|fought back]], leading to the death of Jabba and destruction of the ''Khetanna''.<ref name="RotJ" />

==Personality and traits==
Ardon Crell panicked when Leia Organa threatened to destroy Jabba's Palace with a [[Thermal detonator/Legends|thermal detonator]]. He had [[Color/Legends|black]] [[Hair/Legends|hair]], brown [[Eye/Legends|eyes]], and fair skin.<ref name="RotJ" />

==Equipment==
Ardon Crell wore a [[Jumpsuit/Legends|jumpsuit]], across which he carried an ammunition [[Bandolier/Legends|bandolier]]. He also wore a red headband.<ref name="RotJ" />

==Behind the scenes==
Ardon Crell was created for the [[1983]] film [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']].<ref name="RotJ" /> Prior to the film's [[May 25]] release,<ref name="Year by Year">''[[Star Wars Year By Year: A Visual History, Updated and Expanded Edition]]''</ref> Crell appeared in ''[[Return of the Jedi: The Storybook Based on the Movie]]'',<ref name="Storybook">''[[Return of the Jedi: The Storybook Based on the Movie]]''</ref> released on [[May 12]] of the same year.<ref name="Amazon">{{Amazon|url=Return-Jedi-Storybook-Based-Movie/dp/0394856244|text=Return of the Jedi: The Storybook Based on the Movie}}</ref> The palace scenes featuring Crell were filmed between [[January 25]] and [[February 8]], [[1982]] on Stage 8 at [[Elstree Studios]], and the sail barge interior shots were filmed on Stage 9 between [[February 9]] and [[February 11]].<ref name="Making of">''[[The Making of Return of the Jedi]]''</ref> In [[April]] [[1998]], Crell was first named and given a backstory on a [http://www.starwarsccg.org/cardlists/images/starwars/JabbasPalace-Light/large/ardonvaporcrell.gif card] in ''[[Jabba's Palace Limited]]'', an expansion set of the [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]].<ref name="CCG" />

